commentary: Woakes to Santner, OUT banged in short, and smashed hard out to deep midwicket ... slightly top-edged, Hales circles, and clings onto a brilliant effort! That wasn't easy, he had to make good ground, the ball was dying on him all the time, and he scooped it low to his right with a tumble. He's not the sharpest of England's fielders, but he did well there

commentary: Woakes to Southee, OUT what a stunning take! A slower ball long-hop from Woakes, Southee picked it well enough, thumped it hard and flat towards the midwicket fence, but Bairstow swoops round, one-handed, plucking it out of the air with his best Superman impression! It was the speed that made that special, nothing but a perfectly timed dive would do! And he had to be mindful of tumbling over the rope too. Unbelievably good
